her on the day of Eid, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ala\u0304t al-'\u012adayn lil-Mah\u0323a\u0304mili\u0304 2\/218 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19587,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/ghusl-before-eid-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":5394,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Perform Ghusl before attending Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, used to perform a ritual bath\u00a0on the day of Eid\u00a0before he would depart\u00a0for prayer. Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 609 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi Imam al-Nawawi commented, \"The narrations of Al-Shafi'i and his companions agree upon the recommendation to perform\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36091,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/hasan-taqabbal-allahu-minna\/","url_meta":{"origin":5394,"position":2},"title":"Hasan on Eid: May Allah accept from us and from you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Hawshab ibn \u2018Aqil reported: I met Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, on the day of Eid and I said, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Al-Hasan said, \u201cYes, may Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: al-Du\u2019a\u0304\u2019 li-T\u0323abara\u0304ni 930 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/taqabbal-allahu-minna-minkum\/","url_meta":{"origin":5394,"position":3},"title":"Umar II on Eid: May Allah accept from us and from you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Adham reported: We would say to Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, on the two Eids, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you, O commander of the faithful.\u201d He would return it to us and he did not reject that from us. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19598,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/eid-takbir-imam-arrives\/","url_meta":{"origin":5394,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Pronouncing Takbir until the Imam arrives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would depart to the Eid prayer from the mosque and he would raise his voice, declaring the greatness of Allah until he arrived at the place of prayer. He would continue to exalt Allah until the Imam arrived. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19589,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/seven-five-takbir-salat-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":5394,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Seven and five Takbir in Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn 'Awf reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would pronounce takbir during the Eid prayer seven times before the recitation in the first cycle, and five times before the recitation in the second cycle. Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThis tradition is acted upon by some of the people\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5394","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=5394"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5394\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=5394"}],"wp:term